            <summary><p>12 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark: Is 1425; Qurʾānic text: Q 23:1-25:20 (incomplete); 7 lines per page; Dimensions: 195 x 257mm; Script style: kūfī.</p><p> </p><p>The catalogue of Qurʾān manuscripts of Chester Beatty Library contains the following information (<ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/JXE6ZPW5">Arberry 1967</ref>, p. 11): </p>"29. Juz’ XVIII (incomplete). Twelve folios of firm vellum, measuring 25.7 x 19.5 cm., 7 lines to the page. The script is upright and very regular, fully pointed and vocalized in red, blue, green, and yellow. Verse-endings are indicated by a circular ornament. <hi rend="italic">Alif </hi>is 2.5 cm. high. The first three pages are illuminated in gold. A comparable script is Munajjed 8. See Plate 22. (MS. 1425)" <p/>
                    </summary>
